The article is about a speech given by President Joe Biden at the Ted M. Gallegos Community Center in Albuquerque, New Mexico. The President expressed his support for Governor Lujan Grisham, urging the audience to re-elect her. He emphasized that the upcoming election is a choice between the values represented by Governor Grisham and those of her opponent. The President encouraged the audience to show up and vote. Governor Lujan Grisham also spoke, expressing her gratitude to the people of New Mexico and highlighting the importance of fighting for the community. The event concluded with the President urging the audience to spread faith and offering his blessings.